commit.message:
Update ChangLog with last minute fixes for v4.5

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Fix "non-decreasing" generation id, must increment on each restart

According to the last draft DVMRP v3 RFC, which the genid support is
based on, the generation id should be incremented with each restart.
This so neighboring routers can detect a restart and immediately send
their routing table.

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Fix compat read location and new location for mrouted.genid

Follow-up to #37 in 5438ff3, which somehow failed to fix this issue
properly.  To make matters worse, however, it turns out there are
several Linux systems out there still that has _PATH_VARDB set to
/var/db instead of the FHS standardized /var/lib/misc, so we have
to add a check for that too.

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

man: minor, avoid repeating hard when we mean difficult

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>

Always log (info level) when assuming the IGMP querier role

Figuring out why there are IGMP query problems in a network can be
painful.  This change makes it possible to enable info log level,
which is disabled by default, to see when mrouted assumes the IGMP
querier role.

Signed-off-by: Joachim Wiberg <troglobit@gmail.com>
